Q : Add a column updated_at that auto-updates on row update.
To add a column updated_at that automatically updates whenever a row is modified, use:

ALTER TABLE your_table_name
ADD COLUMN updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP;
What this does:
DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP → sets current time when row is created.
ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP → automatically updates the timestamp whenever the row is updated.

